"title": "8653: importunity, towards God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8653",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Earnestness and perseverance in presenting requests to God on behalf of oneself and others; seen in persistent pleading, faithful intercession and bold appeal.</p>\n<h2>Perseverance in prayer</h2>\n<h3>Persistence in prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:17\">PSA 55:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1-Ps22:2\">PSA 22:1–22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:3\">PSA 86:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:1\">PSA 88:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:9\">PSA 88:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:17\">1TH 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:5\">1TI 5:5</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:7-Matt7:8\">MAT 7:7–7:8</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:9-Luke11:10\">LUK 11:9–11:10</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:1\">LUK 18:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:2-Luke18:8\">LUK 18:2–18:8</a></p>\n<h3>Faithfulness in prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:18\">EPH 6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:9-Rom1:10\">ROM 1:9–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:12\">COL 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:2-1Thess1:3\">1TH 1:2–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:3\">2TI 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Earnestness in prayer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:58\">PSA 119:58</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:1-Ps130:2\">PSA 130:1–130:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:1-Ps55:2\">PSA 55:1–55:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps61:1-Ps61:2\">PSA 61:1–61:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:8\">JON 3:8</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:44\">LUK 22:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7\">HEB 5:7</a></p>\n<h2>Boldness in prayer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:27\">GEN 18:27</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:8\">LUK 11:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:12-Exod33:16\">EXO 33:12–33:16</a>EPH <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:12\">3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a></p>\n<h2>Further examples of importunity in prayer</h2>\n<h3>Repeated requests in prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:22-Gen18:32\">GEN 18:22–18:32</a> <em>Abraham prays for Sodom</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:36-Judg6:40\">JDG 6:36–6:40</a> <em>Gideon asks for assurance</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22-Matt15:28\">MAT 15:22–15:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:25-Mark7:30\">MRK 7:25–7:30</a> <em>a Canaanite woman begs for Jesus Christ's help</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:30-Matt20:31\">MAT 20:30–20:31</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:47-Mark10:48\">MRK 10:47–10:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:38-Luke18:39\">LUK 18:38–18:39</a> <em>Blind men call out to Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:44\">MAT 26:44</a> <em>Jesus Christ prays in Gethsemane</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:10\">MRK 5:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:31\">LUK 8:31</a> <em>Legion begs for mercy</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:8\">2CO 12:8</a> <em>Paul pleads with God to take away his “thorn”.</em></p>\n<h3>Further examples of perseverance in prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:26\">GEN 32:26</a> <em>Jacob wrestles with God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:18\">DEU 9:18</a> <em>Moses fasts and prays because of Israel's sin</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:16\">2SA 12:16</a> <em>David pleads for his sick child</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:28-1Kgs18:29\">1KI 18:28–18:29</a> <em>The prophets of Baal appeal unsuccessfully to their god</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4-Neh1:6\">NEH 1:4–1:6</a> <em>Nehemiah prays for God's people</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:2-Dan10:3\">DAN 10:2–10:3</a> <em>Daniel waits for the interpretation of his vision</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a> <em>Anna looks for God to redeem his people.</em></p>\n<h3>Further examples of earnestness in prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:12-1Sam1:16\">1SA 1:12–1:16</a> <em>Hannah prays for a child</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:22\">1KI 8:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:12\">2CH 6:12</a> <em>Solomon prays at the dedication of the Temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:17-Jas5:18\">JAS 5:17–5:18</a> <em>Elijah prays for rain to cease</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:5\">EZR 9:5</a> <em>Ezra prays about the people's sin</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:2-Isa38:3\">ISA 38:2–38:3</a> <em>Hezekiah prays for healing</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:3\">DAN 9:3</a> <em>Daniel prays for Jerusalem</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:22-Mark5:23\">MRK 5:22–5:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:41-Luke8:42\">LUK 8:41–8:42</a> <em>Jairus asks Jesus Christ to heal his daughter</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:47\">JHN 4:47</a> <em>A nobleman begs Jesus Christ to heal his son</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:5\">ACT 12:5</a> <em>The early church prays for Peter's release from prison.</em></p>",
